[To] Easamau

[NPC Internal] Hi Easamau, do you have another task I can help you with?
[NPC] Easamau: I do have a second task I need done; you will not find it easy, however.
[NPC] Easamau: I need 50,000 tria to save my father from having his home taken away from him by the Hydlaa tax collector, Darphen Wrestele; you can either give him the money or see what other arrangements you can make with him to relieve the debt.
[NPC] Easamau: Will you try to aid me?
[NPC Internal] I will help you.
[NPC] Easamau: Stupendous!
[NPC] Easamau: This is my problem, Darphen Wrestele is the tax collector in Hydlaa, my father Darven Bounash, is a gambler.
[NPC] Easamau: I did not take his family name and moved out to the Bronze Doors area to spare myself the horrors of his reputation.
[NPC] Easamau: He gambled away not only most of my inheritance from my mother but also mortgaged his home to pay his debts, which rise each year.
[NPC] Easamau: He has managed to heap up an enormous debt which I will not be able to pay in the next twenty years of service here as a member of the Sunshine Squadron.
[NPC] Easamau: All the while, as his debts have accumulated, his taxes have gone unpaid.
[NPC Narrate] -Easamau shakes his head and continues.-
[NPC] Easamau: Darphen Wrestele has sent me a dispatch informing me that unless my father can come up with the money soon, he will be forced to sell our home and put something of value to Hydlaa in its place.
[NPC] Easamau: I need you to go there and find a way to relieve the debt.
[NPC] Easamau: If you can make it back to me with a receipt saying the taxes are up to date, I can give you a rare glyph my mother left me in her will.
[NPC] Easamau: Speak with Darphen first.
[NPC] Easamau: I am sure he will want a great deal in return for this tax relief.
[NPC] Easamau: Good tidings, brave soul.

